title: Bollywood Tandoor
reviewr_text: Bollywood is by far the best Indian in Cebu. Their staff is friendly and their dishes are truly succulent and flavorful. If you come on Saturdays they have a belly dance show as well.

title: S&R New York Style Pizza
reviewr_text:
So this place is where you get essentially Costco pizza in Cebu. They offer a pizza with shrimp on it that you can't get in the US. The bread, cheese, and size of the slice are very familiar to those who have tried a Costco slice but the toppings were an interesting change of flavor. If you want you can still get your usual pepperoni, cheese, and combo, but since your in Cebu why not live a little and try something new. 

Just like the Costco pizza in the states, these slices will do the job to satisfy a pizza craving. Nothing to rave about but it will do. Super fast service and a slice of American style pizza at a very cheap price!

reviewer_name: [{"reviewer_name":"Verne A."},{"reviewer_name":"Michael H."},{"reviewer_name":"Sheena Y."},{"reviewer_name":"Terri S."},{"reviewer_name":"Myles C."},{"reviewer_name":"Monz S."}]
reviewr_text:
This is for the Phat Pho at Ayala Mall in Cebu, but I imagine this goes for all in the city as I understand all are under abaca management.  A year and a half ago, I would have given 5 stars.  Now they barely deserve 2.

What changed about their Pho?

They seem to have reduced the portion size while keeping prices the same.  It's broth, it doesn't cost a lot to produce.  

Undercooked slightly hard fettuccini noodles.  

The bean sprouts were already in the bowl and amount seemed much less also.  I wasn't sure if they were even there. 

Broth was not as good as I remember.  

This was my favorite restaurant in all the Philippines and now I don't even want to go back.  This is truly sad and it was something I looked forward to when visiting this city.  I will go to the Banilad location to see if it's the same.  If it is, I'll give my feedback again in person.

title: Parilya
reviewr_text:
This place is own by the cafe laguna restaurant family, So it already has an established reputation for good quality and tasting filipino food. Except this tkme you get the view of the ocean!
My usual favorites are fresh lumpia, grilled tuna belly, and fresh mango shake or freah buko juice if your feeling tropical.
if your not into seafood, try out the pata humba, another traditional filipino fave.

title: Cafe Launderette
reviewr_text:
Fantastically delicious and reasonably priced cafe that's hidden inside a laundromat... crazy but worth the small adventure in finding it! 

Some local friends recommended Cafe Laundrette for their sour Pork Sinigang Soup. Since I love tangy dishes, I checked it out for lunch today. It was DELICIOUS - the broth was amazing and pork was so tender! Wow, I seriously think I found my new favorite soup. 

We also ordered the pork stroganoff, which is not my thing but was also very good. Their winter melon milk tea w/ pearls was also delicious. 

It's two doors down from the Julia's Bakery.

I'll definitely be back... and probably order the soup every time. 

See ya there!

reviewr_text:
I'm in no great position to give a review to this place since i've only been here once and i only ordered a single dish so I will just leave my 2 cents for now.

The ambiance was really good. It's located at the top of Ayala along side all those other great food places. The orange juice was indeed freshly squeezed orange juice! Hooray! The overall taste was i'll have to say very Asian.

title: Luzern Steakhouse
reviewr_text:
What a nice surprise tonight to find the best steak house in Cebu.   The great food and amazing service made for a truly exquisite experience tonight.   Sometimes even the little things can add so much to a meal, and tonight that was the freshly baked warm bread served before our meal.
This hidden gem is worth all five stars except for the fact that parking can be problematic.

title: Pizzeria Michelangelo
reviewr_text:
Maybe my taste for pizza is more toward the pizzas in the states.  I found the pizza here to be very dry tasting.  We ordered 2 pizzas and one white cream pasta.  The pasta was pretty good but very basic flavor of a Alfredo.
I did enjoy the service.  The server was very helpful.  So with good service I give 3 stars.

reviewr_text: Always a favorite when I visit Cebu, I've only failed to eat here on one of my visits. The server's may get annoying as they try to lure you to their stall and block your way, hence, I always choose the stall at the end where there are less people. Over the years, it has also changed dramatically from stalls having individual areas for grilling to one that has a centralised area for grilling, making it less likely for you to leave the area smelling like smoke. The wash area has also been slightly improved though I'd rather bring my wet wipes and alcohol. Be sure to choose the stall you want as though they generally offer the same selection, they have some slight nuances such as perhaps one would have shrimp and prawns, the other would have pork belly and another may not offer seafood at all. Also do note the marinades are heavy on salt so do hydrate as well.

reviewr_text: Love this place. Quaint little atmosphere with simple decor but is very warming. The place is quiet and offers top-notch quality food at a reasonable price. I come here to do stock trading on my laptop, as it is quiet and I have plenty of space at the tables to lay out all my stock analyzing devices.

title: Zark's Burgers
reviewr_text: I noticed this place by chance walking in the mall. It was busy and even today on a monday it was busy so of course i had to give it a try. The place is cramped and their lemononade is blue. From what I can tell, this is their first store in Cebu, but they have many in Manila. I went with the "strikeout" which comes with mushrooms. The burger bun on the thick side, but I appreciate fact that its cooked upon order. The taste is not bad, better than burger king, and the atmosphere is lively. Would have liked more lettuce and tomato, but such are ingredients are sparse on the island haha.

title: Café George
reviewr_text:
I am so happy to that this place has vegan options.  When ur in Cebu, you're in a crowd of meat eaters.

I had the black bean and quinoa burger which was soooo good.

Gotta go back to try the other vegan dishes.

reviewer_name: [{"reviewer_name":"Jonny M."},{"reviewer_name":"Sheena Y."},{"reviewer_name":"Robert N."},{"reviewer_name":"Michael H."},{"reviewer_name":"Totong B."},{"reviewer_name":"Kelsie H."},{"reviewer_name":"Jenny C."},{"reviewer_name":"Swan L."},{"reviewer_name":"Emma D."},{"reviewer_name":"Keisha R."},{"reviewer_name":"Liza M."},{"reviewer_name":"Thomas L."},{"reviewer_name":"Nataraki T."}]
reviewr_text: Really great food and service here. Staff is always pleasant and I like how they introduce themselves and ask for your name. We always get the sisig, crispy pata and sizzling bangus. I'm not a pinakbet fan, but it's actually pretty good here and so is their bagoong. Took my Manila family here who is not really familiar with what's popular to Cebuanos (my Cebu family loves this place). They ended up thoroughly enjoying the food. Only thing is, it may take some time for your food to come out, which is ok because it's all good anyway! Just make sure you have the time. Lastly, their ube Halo Halo is mmmazing! I love ube and I love how they have a large chunk of ube halaya at the bottom PLUS ube ice cream. The macapuno has the right consistency. The corn flakes are a nice touch. The snow-ice is the best! It's so fine and fluffy. So far it's my favorite Halo Halo of all the ones I've tried in the Philippines.

title: Sunburst Fried Chicken
reviewr_text: IMO, this is the best tasting fried chicken. The after taste, the crispiness, the juiciness, hmmm.... They also have expanded their menu to be competitive as there are tons of food business in Cebu. And kinilaw (Ceviche)!!!!! They have many restaurant branches all over Cebu so they're not hard to find. If you're here visiting Cebu, their chicken is a must try.

title: Tymad Bistro
reviewr_text: The croissants are some of the most delicious I've ever had--crunchy on the outside and soft on the inside. They're so good they run out every night so try to come early if possible. Since they open at 7am they're a great place to grab breakfast as the rest of their food is also delicious and well work the trip. Their mango juice is also very fresh.

title: Choobi Choobi
reviewr_text: Great menu but poor service, limited choice of drinks and food barely warm. Nobody refreshes your table or asks if you need another drink. Famous place, but would never eat here again, really poor service and food is 6/10 at best

title: Zubuchon
reviewer_name: [{"reviewer_name":"M A G."},{"reviewer_name":"Jacques I."},{"reviewer_name":"Tellie N."},{"reviewer_name":"Kent H."},{"reviewer_name":"Ron Z."},{"reviewer_name":"Robert N."},{"reviewer_name":"Joey R."},{"reviewer_name":"Lillian C."},{"reviewer_name":"Linda P."},{"reviewer_name":"Benjamin C."},{"reviewer_name":"Cris T."},{"reviewer_name":"David L."},{"reviewer_name":"Kathrine P."},{"reviewer_name":"John A."},{"reviewer_name":"Barry T."},{"reviewer_name":"Aileen B."},{"reviewer_name":"Angeli Y."},{"reviewer_name":"Ian Maren C."},{"reviewer_name":"Katrina E."},{"reviewer_name":"Geoffrey U."}]
reviewr_text:
Personally don't understand the hype for Zubuchon.
As someone who's lived in cebu her entire life, not to mention has eaten lunch a good number of times, I must disagree; Zubuchon gives lechon a very bland flavor. I don't feel much but the texture once I munch on it. 
If anything, it is slightly average, or very much below the line. There are plenty of other lechon places in cebu where you can truly taste a REAL Cebuano lechon. Just being honest

title: Shawarma Gourmet
reviewr_text:
First visit to this restaurant... food is ok
I ordered a falafel sandwich and they charged me extra to get lettuce on my sandwich instead of cabbage... tahini was as thick as water.... 
also I ordered a beef shawarma sandwich and they charged me extra when I asked for extra onion... AND they charged me 10% extra as a service charge 
2nd time I was there I placed an order to go and this time also they charged me 10% extra for service charge... I told the cashier I am not dining in so why the extra 10% for service charge? I am taking the food out so you should not charge me 10% extra? She said the extra 10% service charge applies for all orders either dine in or take out... I canceled my order and left.... this was the only restaurant I ever visited in the Philippines that charges service charge... I think the owner is a very greedy person and have no business understanding to charge this extra charge in the first place and I think it's very stupid to charge the extra charge on to go orders... 
I will never visit this restaurant again and I don't recommend dealing with greedy owner as this owner.

title: Grand Majestic
reviewr_text: Pretty good chinese food. I'm not sure if it's the best around since i haven't had a taste of some of the other well known chinese places, but if you want something easy to get by then Majestic is the place to go. They have branches in both SM Cebu and SM Seaside, as well as in Ayala. And their service is FASSST. Like literally your waiter could have just taken your order and they'll be back within 10 minutes to put food on your table.

title: Tim Ho Wan
reviewer_name: [{"reviewer_name":"Phil S."},{"reviewer_name":"Marissa S."},{"reviewer_name":"Toyo M."},{"reviewer_name":"Cynthia Q."},{"reviewer_name":"Tracy N."},{"reviewer_name":"Ray J."}]
reviewr_text: First experience at a Michelin starred restaurant! Dim sum is usually not one of my first cuisine picks, though I couldn't pass up the chance to dine at this restaurant. Small menu, with photos of each menu item - nice touch. The pork buns. Oh, the pork buns. These are what earned this restaurant it's Michelin star. Traditionally steamed, but Tim Ho Wan got it right by baking them. Perfection! Take note, filling is on the sweeter side - if that doesn't suit your tastes. Congee was ok, not too salty considering the salted duck egg. The wasabi shrimp salad dumplings were delicious! I often find that deep fried dumplings at dim sum restaurants are often too greasy as if they've absorbed the oil or tasting like old/stale fryer oil. Not the case here. Gailan was steamed just right and still crunchy. Everything else was delicious. Food came out quick, and more or less all at the same time. Happy we came. Great meal overall. Only regret is overeating (as per usual) and not saving room to try dessert.

title: Sans Rival
reviewr_text:
Sans Rival is a terrific place to satisfy your sweettooth!!  They are located on the ground floor of Robinsons Galleria in Cebu City, Philippines.  You can dine in or take out.  We did both.

My wife and her friend each had a slice of Yema cake.  I had a slice of Mango Cloud cake.
My Mango Cloud was alright.  Tasted a bit dry, and the filling was just alright.  Probably would not order again.  The Yema cake was yummy!  

We got Silvanas for take out.  They were supposed to give it to us frozen like the package says, but it was not frozen.  Honestly, though, that did not bother me.  It still tasted awesome!!!

They have other food besides desserts.  Seriously, though, I think the desserts our the items to purchase at Sans Rival.

title: STK ta Bai!
reviewr_text: After much anticipation my fiancee and I arrived at 7:30 on a wdnesday evening.  The placecwas not busy in the slightest and our order was taken quickly. That was the last decent service of the night! My fiancee's meal was brought and then the waiting began one hour later and our starters of baked scallops, as well as my meal, had yet to arrive. After asking several times, my meal was produced, but still no scallops. Another 30 minutes pass before I give ip and ask for the bill, which took 15 minutes to arrive and they tried to charge me for the scallops and a drink we did not order. Another 15 minutes pass before a waitress stops to ask if I would like cancel the scallops and drink which we did not order the final insult was the refusal to call a taxi for us. Good food, horrible service

There's ramen, meat, udon, hot pot and even dessert and I do enjoy the free green tea.

title: Japanese Carinderia Haru
reviewr_text:
This place is a great find for this area. Its
not as good as the expensive restaurants but its not bad considering location and price. It was my first time trying yakisoba so I don't have anything to compare it to.
The tokoyaki is not bad, though they have squid instead of octopus. Not as good as sachi or osaka takoyaki but pretty good. If I am in the area I would definitely stop by fkr a meal. It is street food ambiance since you are pretty much eating ln sidewalk and their kiosk is located under set a stairs. Clever
move on part of owner.

title: Adventure Cafe
reviewr_text:
I can't say anything about the adventure part, but I was able to dine in for some merienda with their special suman and tsocolate with mango. It was a great pick-me-up during a long drive from Bantayan with its sweet sticky rice and hot piping chocolate which is placed in a little pouring jar. The mango shake was a little bit too sweet for my liking, but the guyabano shake definitely is a mild but refreshing drink for the hot humid weather. Service was excellent and fast. Next time I'll try the zip lining through the mountains of Cebu, just you wait!!!

CR available downstairs.

Zipline available and cafe with full menu.
Senior discount available.
Unfortunately uses plastic straw!

Mangaon ta!

title: Laguna Garden Cafe
reviewer_name: [{"reviewer_name":"Kimberly T."},{"reviewer_name":"PatrickJ T."},{"reviewer_name":"Toyo M."},{"reviewer_name":"Ken S."},{"reviewer_name":"Kelsie H."},{"reviewer_name":"Sherwin T."},{"reviewer_name":"Andrew M."},{"reviewer_name":"Monz S."}]

title: Casa Verde
reviewer_name: [{"reviewer_name":"Jay K."},{"reviewer_name":"Thunder H."},{"reviewer_name":"Joe T."},{"reviewer_name":"Joey R."},{"reviewer_name":"Ray J."},{"reviewer_name":"Dale E."},{"reviewer_name":"Sheika G."},{"reviewer_name":"Jodie S."},{"reviewer_name":"Monz S."}]
reviewr_text:
The original when I think of ribs and steak in Cebu, at least for me. This is where the Noel Family made their name in quality and service. Some say it's a TGIF, but to me it's vastly different. TGIF is an over-glorified restaurant that is ludicrous in their menu prices with what I consider to be subpar cuts of meat. Casa Verde excels where most other bbq joints in the greater Cebu area do not.

Each time I visit the ancestral homeland, I always stop by here and grab a plate. This review is long overdue, a good 3 yrs since I've eaten there. I was just looking at photos and became nostalgic so decided to see if Casa Verde would appear on Yelp.

Yes there are plenty of other places to get your BBQ fix in Cebu, but it's more "Asian Style" than western proper. Each have their nuances, for Casa Verde, it was that "American" portion of big, bold, and meaty. First time I came here was in 2008/9, I felt happy and intimidated by the copious amounts of meat I had shoved in my mouth. Fast forward to 2013, stopped by here again and waited it out in line. Monday night (photo date shows it to be a Monday) and for me it was not busy at all, rather surprised because in past experiences Casa Verde is always packed especially from Thur-Sat. Ms. Seattle ordered some type of salad (really?!) but I do recall that was quickly swapped as she proceeded to eat my steak and grilled shrimp. This was 3 yrs ago, but wading through past memories is always a good thing, especially when it pertains to good food.

title: Soba Kamakura
reviewr_text: Best soba in Cebu..even in the whole country! The place is a small private kitchen and is currently limited to only 6 persons (4 at the counter and 2 at the table). You need to make an advance reservation if you want to eat at this place since it's impossible to just walk-in and hope to find an available seat. You can either call or book online to place for a reservation. The ingredients are carefully sourced and picked fresh everyday. Their soba is made to order, it is made fresh in front of you. The ingredients for their soba is imported directly from Hokkaido, Japan and is flown directly from there and not through sea cargo(since shipping it by sea and risk exposing it to heat would ruin/change the distinct characteristics of the soba). There's also a decent choice of beverages including liquors like sake and some beers. I definitely would go back and would recommend this place to anyone. Don't expect the price to be cheap though but the price you pay is worth every cent.

title: Orange Karenderia
reviewr_text: Excellent food very moderate price. Great value and atmosphere. Try the Mango shake (not on the menu) but very good.

title: Cali Shrimp
reviewr_text:
This place has the neighborhood vibe. The star dish is the the cajun shrimp, but they also offer balbacua, beef in broth, lechon and have a neighboring food stand that offers barbecue. 
 At the current time, food can run out fast so go early.

title: Pink Heaven
reviewr_text: This is a bakery and bistro. A bakery that serves mango eclairs.  Looks fancy and the drinks are fancy. 120 pesos for a ginger lemongrass drink.

title: Mooon Cafe
reviewr_text:
I used to be a big fan of Mooon Cafe.  The last time I went to one of their branches, though, I was not impressed.  There was no more "Wow" factor.  When my sister n'law suggested Mooon Cafe close to Parkmall, I was all for it!

We beat the dinner rush because only two other tables had patrons.  Our group of six was seated right away.  The colorful decor reminds me of Mexican restaurants at home.  Much of the menu is Mexican cuisine inspired.

A few folks in our party ordered Frozen Iced Tea.  It was different and tasty.  My niece ordered her other favorite two items as well.  A Pasta entree and Pumpkin soup.  She finished them both.  My nieces shared the Amigos Platter which included salsa, chips, fries, a quesedilla sort of thing, and onion rings.  It was okay.  Wifey said her Tuna Belly entree was pretty good.  My Mooonte Christo sandwich was okay too.  Was truly expecting more flavor, though.

It will probably be awhile before I return to Mooon Cafe again.  Cebu has so many good restaurants, and I still have to give others a try.

title: The Pyramid
reviewr_text: Came here for the first time with friends and the ambience is wonderful but the service was way too slow! I ordered a Caesar salad and waited for good 45 mins. The waitress told me that they had to boil the egg which I think is ridiculous. We order more food and drinks and they came in quite longer than the usual and the food was not that spectacular.  We were at the restaurant for more than 3 hours because we waited for one more friend and decided to order coffee "Americano" and that took about 30 mins. then waitress told us that the machine is broken so we ended up closing our tab and left to another coffee spot. We had dinner at 7:00 pm and pretty much left at 11 pm very dissatisfied with the experience.

title: Red House Shabu Shabu
reviewer_name: [{"reviewer_name":"Colby W."},{"reviewer_name":"Sheena Y."},{"reviewer_name":"Brian J."},{"reviewer_name":"Thomas K."},{"reviewer_name":"Angela L."},{"reviewer_name":"Monz S."}]
reviewr_text:
This place is great! 

Red house is a very close walk from where we stayed. It's down an awkward little side street, not particularly close to any other restaurants.

It's Shabu Shabu, so we got to do our own cooking while there. They set a large pot of basic soup in front of you, you start ordering anything you want and cook those items in the soup. 

We ordered mushrooms, thinly cut beef and pork, shrimp, and something that looked liked Bok Choy. All delicious. 

Be sure to cook the thinly sliced meat for no longer than 10 seconds, or the time it takes to loose it's red color. 

They also have a table in the middle of the restaurant where you can bring back toppings to your table. White and green onions, garlic, soy sauce, vinegar, and chili oil.

title: Luzern Steakhouse
reviewr_text: This is probably my favorite steakhouse in cebu. The steaks are delicious! The servers are also accommodating and nice. Even though we didn't have reservations, they still tried to give us seats while the reserved tables are not yet occupied. This place could get crowded even on weekdays thats why reservations are helpful.

title: Cafe Marco
reviewr_text: My favorite buffet in town...love their sashimi  they have wide array of dishes to choose from...variety of dimsum to choose from, and taste good too. Make sure you save room for dessert coz' you definitely wouldn't want to let it pass. Perfect for family and even business dinners.

title: Zubuchon
reviewer_name: [{"reviewer_name":"M A G."},{"reviewer_name":"Jacques I."},{"reviewer_name":"Tellie N."},{"reviewer_name":"Kent H."},{"reviewer_name":"Ron Z."},{"reviewer_name":"Robert N."},{"reviewer_name":"Joey R."},{"reviewer_name":"Lillian C."},{"reviewer_name":"Linda P."},{"reviewer_name":"Benjamin C."},{"reviewer_name":"Cris T."},{"reviewer_name":"David L."},{"reviewer_name":"Kathrine P."},{"reviewer_name":"John A."},{"reviewer_name":"Barry T."},{"reviewer_name":"Aileen B."},{"reviewer_name":"Angeli Y."},{"reviewer_name":"Ian Maren C."},{"reviewer_name":"Katrina E."},{"reviewer_name":"Geoffrey U."}]
reviewr_text:
The Famous Lechon House in the Queen City of the South - Cebu, Philippines! Cebu is known for the famous and the best tasting Lechon in the Philippines and Zubuchon has proved that fact! The Lechon is stuffed with the finest spices and Cooked traditionally using Wood Charcoal (commonly known as Uling) in medium heat for 3-4 hours. You can smell the Lechon essence even from 50 feet away while its still cooking.

For a very tasty treat of this delicious Lechon, it should be served fresh from the "open air oven" (Lechon is cooked in an open space where available. Most Filipinos cook Lechon at their open backyards). Knife please, cut open the stomach part and let the "Lechon Spice Soup" out! This mouthwatering part is the best. Get some of the crispy skin part near the neck or the back part, dip it in the Lechon Spice Soup - taste and savour this heavenly Filipino delicacy!

You haven't taste the Philippines if you don't try the Zubuchon Lechon! Have an Epic Lechon Meal!

title: Kuya J's Restaurant
reviewr_text:
The must have on our list is kare kare! I think theirs is a healthy version of kare kare. Not too oily. But i think they should try serving the sweet style bagoong.  In the US, most of the bagoong are serve sweet. 
The customer service is great. We were outside looking for the menu, the attendant came to us and explain their menu. How's the portion on every item we ask since we are only dining for two.
Over all, it's a good experience.

main: Ipar’s Restaurante Y Bar De Tapas
title: Ipar's Restaurante Y Bar De Tapas
reviewr_text:
Service was great. Food was great also. 
Had paella for solo. It was great but needs to be a tad bigger. Other than that all my party was satisfied. Also really nice  furniture especially the tables.

title: KPub BBQ
reviewr_text: We are a family of four adults (vacation from the USA) and decided to go with the unlimited order selection which allows you to stay and order with unlimited time or food selection. Overall, we can say that the BBQ is OK, the seafood is terrible, and the sides was a good try which we compare to great Korean restaurants in Ellicott City, Maryland and Honolulu, Hawaii. The service started fine and we received all the side dishes and meats as listed on the menu. Then after this initial delivery of food, the waiter serving our table decided that he was no longer going to serve us and service other bigger party tables instead. We ordered some BBQ and he never came back which after about 30+ minutes I decided enough is enough and had to talk to manager about the neglect of servicing our table.  This is by far the worst service my family and I ever experienced from any restaurant we've been to. Also, after the initial set of BBQ meats served, they began pushing the lesser quality meat and surely slowed the service as a tactic to slow down ordering anymore BBQ. For example, I would try and order the short ribs (Kalbi) but they kept bringing a beef tip that had this big bone instead which was definitely not short ribs. I would not recommend this place to anyone. The only thing that we actually enjoyed was the live band playing. Other than that, don't waste your money here!

title: Sunburst
reviewer_name: [{"reviewer_name":"Britt H."},{"reviewer_name":"Keith A."},{"reviewer_name":"Nina M."},{"reviewer_name":"Stewart O."},{"reviewer_name":"Joey R."},{"reviewer_name":"Michael C."}]
reviewr_text:
Every time I visit Cebu, my very first meal is at Sunburst Fried Chicken! The restaurant may look old and tired but it is always crowded. Here, you can enjoy your fried chicken meal with other Filipino dishes like pansit, sizzling bangus or sinigang at affordable prices. For merienda, they offer sandwiches and combo meals. But, honestly, you go here for the Fried Chicken. That's all you need to remember. Fried. Chicken.

I always order the Classic chicken meal. It's 3 pieces of delicious, crispy-on-the-outside-juicy-on-the-inside fried chicken and comes complete with rice, thick french fries and coleslaw on the side. All that for only Php178 (3.81USD)! No need for gravy! All you need to do is mix ketchup and Worcestershire sauce with a little bit of hot sauce. Also, when you're here, you must order their legendary Crispy Chicken Skin! It's always the very thing that runs out though. So, I usually order the next best thing: Fried Chicken Necks! You'll get a plate of 12 pieces with potato chips. YUM!

When in Cebu, eat here and you will not go to KFC or even Jollibee. They are the BEST place for Fried Chicken in Cebu! Tip: Don't be shy! Use your hands to eat ever bit of chicken. ;)

title: Gerry's Grill
reviewer_name: [{"reviewer_name":"Val Y."},{"reviewer_name":"Erika R."},{"reviewer_name":"Paula C."},{"reviewer_name":"Michael C."},{"reviewer_name":"Dfrancisco G."},{"reviewer_name":"Phil O."}]
reviewr_text:
Gerry's Grille - Cebu serves tried and tested Sinigang and Sisig in record time. We waited for less than 10 minutes amd voila! Dinner is served! 

The place is spacious with ample seating area. If there are seats available, you will be ushered inside and be allowed to pick your preferred seats. 

The service crew were very attentive and courteous too!

title: La Vie in the Sky
reviewr_text: My new favorite spot in the phillipines. I'm so excited about this place I can hardly bear it.  You feel like you might be in Paris when you come in. I've been to the first one and fell in love and now that this one is here with the fabulous decor and views to die for I will be here every time I come to the phillipines.

title: Seafood Island
reviewr_text: The chicken inasal they gave us was undercooked. It had blood in it and they mistakenly gave my new cooked chicken inasal at the table beside ours. There's more, when the waiter gave my new chicken inasal, there was another dish (which I ordered) that he was carrying. He was about to leave the table with our dish but we told him that it was ours. I swear like he doesn't know what he's doing and it was irritating.

title: Tongara Ramen
reviewr_text:
One of the best ramen in Cebu. Their broth is very flavorful and their noodles are just right. I like their tantan ramen, tongara ramen, and tsukemen. If you like to order additional noodles, you can. I always order extra chasu here, their chasu is really good. I definitely would recommend this place to anyone.

Update: They offer junior bowls now; which is about half the size of their regular bowl of ramen. So far they have been consistent in their cooking as well.

title: Isla Sugbo Seafood City

reviewr_text: Very clean and nice atmosphere.  You pick the fish you want and how you want it prepared.  They catch it and cook it for you.  Seafood lovers paradise!

title: Off Roads Cafe
reviewr_text: Before the urban sprawl around this area, this place existed serving coffee, sandwiches, and cookies. One of the first places to offer open air space on top of building. Still manages to be.a chill place despite the business outside. I like their cappucino and chocolate or almond cookies. their club sandwijch is ham and egg with more bread haha But prices are reasonable and bave two hour wifi available.

title: House of Lechon
reviewer_name: [{"reviewer_name":"Diego R."},{"reviewer_name":"Winlee W."},{"reviewer_name":"Carissa C."},{"reviewer_name":"Katrina C."},{"reviewer_name":"Edwin R."},{"reviewer_name":"Keith A."},{"reviewer_name":"Jerry H."},{"reviewer_name":"Val Y."},{"reviewer_name":"Evee N."},{"reviewer_name":"Joan N."},{"reviewer_name":"Gloria C."},{"reviewer_name":"Christy S."},{"reviewer_name":"Lina C."},{"reviewer_name":"Mark H."},{"reviewer_name":"Jonnah M."},{"reviewer_name":"Derek W."},{"reviewer_name":"Phil S."},{"reviewer_name":"Paulamertha A."},{"reviewer_name":"Benedict A."},{"reviewer_name":"Lynne C."}]
reviewr_text: I heard that if I wanted the best Lechon (roasted pork), House of Lechon is the place to go. Needless to say, I was NOT disappointed! Came with a few work friends and we got the normal Lechon, spicy Lechon, some cheese sticks, scallops, rice, veggies, and some type of grilled fish (can't recall exactly). I thought everything was so incredibly delicious! The Lechon was so tender and paired perfectly with the sauce that was provided! I was surprisingly impressed with the cheese sticks too! If you're ever in Cebu, I would really suggest you make a stop!

title: Café George
reviewr_text: Food here is good for sharing. A new dining experience which is really healthy and organic. Café George also has a branch at Ayala by the name Oh George. Service is usually slow because they have customers so be sure to come early or whenever you're not yet hungry.  enjoy!

title: Ramen Dojo
reviewr_text:
I was pleasantly suprised. I came in expecting the worsr since this is kind of a fast food chain ramen joint. A ramen bowl at 150 pesos seems unheard of, so of course I had to give it a try.
The broth does not taste like it has a lot of ingredients like the expensive places, but what ingredients that were placed can be tasted, especially the fresh ones. The pork was tender and even more tender than ikkousha ramen cebu! The gyoza was really basic but edible, and if you opt for side order of plain rice at 25 pesos its a great meal!
I will definitely be stoppibg by from time to time for a budget meal to satisy the ramen craving.

title: Hukad sa Golden Cowrie
reviewer_name: [{"reviewer_name":"Jonny M."},{"reviewer_name":"Sheena Y."},{"reviewer_name":"Robert N."},{"reviewer_name":"Michael H."},{"reviewer_name":"Totong B."},{"reviewer_name":"Kelsie H."},{"reviewer_name":"Jenny C."},{"reviewer_name":"Swan L."},{"reviewer_name":"Emma D."},{"reviewer_name":"Keisha R."},{"reviewer_name":"Liza M."},{"reviewer_name":"Thomas L."},{"reviewer_name":"Nataraki T."}]

title: 10 Doves Street
reviewer_name: [{"reviewer_name":"Kristen T."},{"reviewer_name":"Sheena Y."},{"reviewer_name":"Hazel L."},{"reviewer_name":"ravi b."},{"reviewer_name":"Katrina E."},{"reviewer_name":"Toyo M."},{"reviewer_name":"Myles C."}]
reviewr_text:
So good! Came here as a late night treat and had their desserts and hot drinks with the fam. Although the weather is hot and sticky, the restaurant is cold that you'd rather opt for something to keep you warm while enjoying a warm chocolate cake. In fact, they make a variety of American desserts but also a mix of pinoy favorites (Ube! Pandan! Mango! Yehey!). In that instance, I saw their pandan gulaman and had to try... It blew my mind! Lots of delicious jellies in a nice creamy constancy in a small glass jar. Really nice touch there. In the states the (Asian) puddings are usually the typical mango and milk flavor, but Pinas, you got it down! My sweet tooth was fulfilled and I am wanting more!

Love the space. Very cheery and bright. Great spot to bring your girlfriends, family, or a date if you're a big sweets fan. There's plenty of tables to accommodate.

Finally, the hot matcha latte really balanced the dessert. I have no complaints here. The customer service was excellent too.

Open late!

CR available. Super clean!

Mangaon ta!

reviewr_text:
Second time here. Came back because French toast was fantastic. Well.......the second time me and my wife got a couple of omelettes. Not impressed and the breakfast potatoes were from at least 2 days ago. Cold and hard. Also ordered fresh orange juice. I guess they didn't have enough oranges so they added water to fill the glass. . 

Unfortunately will not return a third time.

title: Zubuchon
reviewer_name: [{"reviewer_name":"M A G."},{"reviewer_name":"Jacques I."},{"reviewer_name":"Tellie N."},{"reviewer_name":"Kent H."},{"reviewer_name":"Ron Z."},{"reviewer_name":"Robert N."},{"reviewer_name":"Joey R."},{"reviewer_name":"Lillian C."},{"reviewer_name":"Linda P."},{"reviewer_name":"Benjamin C."},{"reviewer_name":"Cris T."},{"reviewer_name":"David L."},{"reviewer_name":"Kathrine P."},{"reviewer_name":"John A."},{"reviewer_name":"Barry T."},{"reviewer_name":"Aileen B."},{"reviewer_name":"Angeli Y."},{"reviewer_name":"Ian Maren C."},{"reviewer_name":"Katrina E."},{"reviewer_name":"Geoffrey U."}]
reviewr_text:
I came here because I wanted to sample different lechons in Cebu.

Like Joey, I've also had a lot of Cebu friends saying it's not authentic but just try it anyway. So here I ended up trying just for the experience.

The service was probably one of the best at any lechon place I've been to (I guess it's the only place which actually charges you a service charge).

The food is that they serve is definitely photogenic - being that the owner is a food blogger from Manilla, that doesn't surprise me. 

Would I return, not sure - but I do like that it's close to Mango Square, so it's a good eating place before going partying I guess. 

But despite the food being good and I also like boneless lechon - I prefer something more of a  "local" feel (that local cebuano people enjoy). After all, "When in Rome, do as the Romans do"

But I do love the Kamias shake at Zubachon though.

So verdict, come here for the awesome experience, while still eating good food, and make sure you try the kamias shake.

title: Delice Recipe
reviewr_text:
My friends brought me here for my birthday dinner  and I thoroughly enjoyed it.

Food was tops; flavorful and satisfying. Servers were pleasant. A bit on the shy side but definitely not lacking in service and hospitality.  Price vs quantity is average and affordable esp. since the location and ambiance is actually quite dazzling. 

Loved the city lights and I enjoyed the cool outdoor breeze.

title: Choobi Choobi
reviewr_text: My friend who lives in Cebu brought me here for a taste of some quality seafood and I was not disappointed. We ordered the Choobi Choobi fried rice, 1.5 pounds of garlic shrimp, baked scallops and soup. As a drinkI got a lychee shake. Notably for the shrimp we asked for the backs to be opened and cleaned and the heads to be removed. Overall I loved the meal and we were both stuffed at the end of it (rather we couldn't finish it). Everything from the scallops to the shrimp and rice were excellent and I can see myself definitely coming back next time I'm in Cebu. What I particularly liked about the scallops was they were baked in cheese which helped flavour it as well.

title: Salinas
reviewr_text:
This resto is a new addition and owned by the same ones who own Golden Cowrie and what's best is that you can crossover your orders between the two restaurants! They are located side by side. That in itself is great!

The food was quite tasty as to be expected, and for a group of fourteen people, they were able to accommodate us easily during a Monday dinner. We ordered 3 meal bundles (2 x 1400+ and 1,200+) from Golden Cowrie and the Vegetable Sisig and Pinaupong Manok from Salinas. Surprised with the bill total because for the sumptuous feast which we consumed, we still had change for the P5,000.-

So, we made up for the great service and yummy food by leaving a 12% in gratuity. Will definitely eat here again when we visit them. 

Must try if you visit (Lahug) Cebu.

reviewr_text: I searched the Internet for a local breakfast diner near our hotel & found this. Ordered eggs Benedict & bacon silog with extra sausage & pleasantly surprised. The pancakes on the side was fluffy & good , it's like a "taba Ching Ching " version of the regular one. The place caters to students & young crowd, feels like Starbucks without the usual pesky hangers-on. It's right behind Burger King in case you get lost. Good parking space. Highly recommend to those looking for tasty meal to start your day.  Oh, the staff is helpful & very charming, gives a smile to weary travelers like us! Thank you Birdseed & please don't change!

title: Laguna Garden Cafe
reviewer_name: [{"reviewer_name":"Kimberly T."},{"reviewer_name":"PatrickJ T."},{"reviewer_name":"Toyo M."},{"reviewer_name":"Ken S."},{"reviewer_name":"Kelsie H."},{"reviewer_name":"Sherwin T."},{"reviewer_name":"Andrew M."},{"reviewer_name":"Monz S."}]

title: Shakey's
reviewr_text:
It used to be super weird customer service for a US citizen. When they would repeat my order for accuracy, they'd say "I see you ordered our delicious hot mojos guaranteed to satisfy your craving, a delicious cold coke to satisfy that thirst." That seems to be gone (thank god) on this trip.

As far as pizza goes in the PH, this is one of the better pizzas. They have a really good crust that I actually crave each time I come. The sauce is not sweet as I've found at other pizzas places. 

The mojos (deep fried potato slices) are frankly delicious and guaranteed to satisfy your craving *dang it!! It caught on!!* they are  delicious.

I don't eat chicken but hear they have good chicken.  All fried chicken in the PH comes with gravy. I'm sure that's a good thing. I've never said no to gravy.

Their hot sauce I absolutely love. I try to steal a bottle every time I'm there. I've been caught at customs with too many before and had to throw some away....ok, it was really an accident. I forgot I had some on my carry on and you can't bring open liquids on the plane. But the sauce is very delicious

title: La Bella
reviewr_text: Came here for dinner with friends.  I had a salad while they had the pizza.  The prices are pretty steep especially for the salad.  300 pesos just for vegetables mix together is a rip off.  You're better off ordering the pizza or pasta.

title: Sachi
reviewer_name: [{"reviewer_name":"Toyo M."},{"reviewer_name":"Sheena Y."},{"reviewer_name":"Ed T."},{"reviewer_name":"Keisha R."},{"reviewer_name":"Myles C."},{"reviewer_name":"Chris S."}]

title: Tazza Cafe
reviewr_text:
Located right outside the lobby of Tsai Hotel, we rushed in as hunger struck. We were staying at Tsai and saw adverts stating that guests get a 15% discount, so we decided why not.

You order at the front then wait for your food to arrive at your table. We advised the cashier we stayed at Tsai and showed them our room key, they had another promo going on where you buy a drink and a meal you get dessert for 1 peso. We opted for the meal+drink promo, apparently you can only choose either or for the promos. Either you do the 15% off for being a Tsai Hotel guest or you choose the combo promo, you can't have both. 

We ordered chicken parmesan, chicken pesto (creamy), a latte, hot tea, strawberry cake, and chocolate cheesecake. The spaghetti for the chicken parmesan packed flavor. You can taste every bit of garlic.. yum! Chicken was moist and tender in the inside and crispy out. The chicken pesto was equally as good. Chicken was also moist and tender, sauce was of good consistency. The strawberry cake was off the chain, it was so soft and you can actually taste the strawberry flavor. Cake was of good portion. The chocolate cheesecake bar was ok, the size was more on the side of like 1 bite or 2, but the bar itself was also moist. 

I'd say Tazza is of convenient location if staying at Tsai and will come back again to try their other menu items.

title: Matia's BBQ
reviewr_text:
Definitely a MUST try in Cebu!

Matia's BBQ is a family style type of outdoor seating barbecue spot. You order a bunch of different meats, you get hanging rice, soy sauce/vinegar/spices, and enjoy for a reasonable price! My cousins suggested to get the mango shake because it's sweet and delicious, and they weren't wrong! I recommend getting bottled water or soda with your meal. My favorite was the red sausage!

title: Timeout Sports Bar & Resto
reviewr_text: Skip it. It's a place that caters to Americans.  San Miguel light is more expensive than what you can find elsewhere.

title: AA BBq
reviewer_name: [{"reviewer_name":"Anneke D."},{"reviewer_name":"Thu N."},{"reviewer_name":"Gee F."},{"reviewer_name":"Trina T."},{"reviewer_name":"Mike M."},{"reviewer_name":"Stephen B."}]
reviewr_text: Took the inlaws here for a late dinner. We ordered the steamed Lapu Lapu, pansit and some BBQ chicken. The overall meal was actually pretty good. My only complaint is the stray cat that was trying to get a quick bite and the annoying ants..I guess that is expected when eating freestyle outdoors.

title: Everything Yummy
reviewer_name: [{"reviewer_name":"Pier View P."},{"reviewer_name":"Brian J."},{"reviewer_name":"Jo Anne G."},{"reviewer_name":"Yna C."}]
reviewr_text: Clean and cozy atmosphere.   They recommended the ribs but I did not have that large of apatite at the time.  So I got the prawn gambas with the salsa rice.  They were very good together.  The shrimp was a good size and full of flavor.  This is a great place for lunch or dinner.

title: Handuraw
reviewr_text: Great but looks like they are closed.   Typical Filipino fashion no sign up nothing.  Parking is odd and I hope they open soon so I can get some of that ice cold beer.

title: Hai Shin Lou
reviewr_text: Amazing 5 star service from Ronald and staff last night. Lots of large tables for families. Hot jasmine tea, iced tea, and beer were the choices for beverages. We ordered beef minced egg drop soup, fried rice, noodles, spare ribs, and deep fried shrimp. Everything from start to finish was perfect. We opted for snow balls for dessert which is a soft, coconut, with custard like filling. Awesome way to end our meal. Definitely recommend if you're in the area.

title: Craft Cafebar
reviewr_text: Stopped by on Wednesday night and the place was hopping due to Beer Pong Tourney.  I signed up and had a lot of fun in double elimination tourney.    Staff quite nice and the drink list is extensive.  They also have a nice selection of craft beers mostly from a local brewery called Cebruery.  Stopped in around 1:30 PM on Friday and it was quiet except for the 3 employees here.  Music is at perfect volume for conversation. This will probably become a regular place on my stops in Cebu from now on.  Pizza, burgers and Greek food all within 1minute walking.  Free wi-fi.   This is like the Starbucks of craft beer enthusiasts.

title: Fujinoya
reviewr_text: The staff seems to be only accomodating to women, I guess if i were a male wait staff i would do the same. Wifi is limited, but despite the inattentive service and bad upsell to meals, I have to admit the gateau ganache tasted excellent. Not sure what the actual one tastes like but this one tasted special, i highly recommend it.

title: Minnan Chinese Cuisine
reviewr_text: Till now, it's the best restaurant I want in Cebu. It's located in the city center, perfect for me! Saw a post on the Window, "best of Cebu", deserves it!

title: Maya Mexican Restaurant
reviewer_name: [{"reviewer_name":"Susan D."},{"reviewer_name":"Elee J."},{"reviewer_name":"Bobby L."},{"reviewer_name":"Verne A."},{"reviewer_name":"Marco F."},{"reviewer_name":"Jay H."},{"reviewer_name":"Randy H."},{"reviewer_name":"Becky C."},{"reviewer_name":"john b."},{"reviewer_name":"Jorge B."}]

title: Domings Ngohiong
reviewr_text:
This is a hometown/ word of mouth place. It is street food, but this particular place holds a lot of sentiment to the locals and they say its all about the sauce.

Ngohiong is kind of like a fried egg roll but the filling is simpler usually from part of coconut plant i believe. They also offer fried chicken which has a simple coating, you can choose from what they call "bisaya" native chicken which is smaller in size and like a free range versus the "bantris" which is bigger size and the grocery kind.

The place is only open from 730am to 130pm. So if you want to try a local favorite, come and try. Take note, the place is located in Fairlane Village., part pf a housing development.pp

title: Kusina Uno
reviewr_text:
Kusina Uno claims to be the home of Cebu's Best Pochero and that's not far away from the truth because they definitely serve one of the best-tasting pochero I've ever tasted!

They also serve popular Filipino dishes like humba, mechado, and even noodles and they all come in huge servings!

Perfect for the entire family so when you're in Cebu and needs to make an impression, bring them here.

title: Bo's Coffee
reviewr_text: This place seems nicer inside than most locations. They offer breakfast meals and also take credit cards. The  place feels spacious and the interior decor.is notewortjy.

title: Ulli's

main: Murray’s New Orleans Bourbon Street Steak and Oysters
title: Murray's New Orleans Bourbon Street Steak and Oysters
KAYU: Kitchen + Bar
reviewr_text:
Cute little restaurant located in a residential area. 

Their menu is simple which is great then you don't get confused what to order. 

A must get is the duck confit and the Angus beef on a skillet. It's soooooo good.

The duck was soft and the beef was soft too.  Flavors were good.  I also enjoyed the quinoa salad. A must try if ur in cebu

Well worth going to if you are looking for a place to satisfy cravings that you can't get elsewhere at a decent price.

reviewr_text: If you love pochero of all kinds then this is the place to have it.  I've never seen sizzling pochero until I came here.  Lots of other food choices to order from but pochero soup and sizzling pochero is a must order! Plus the staff is nice.

title: Paolito's
reviewr_text: I love the spanish era decor, but the food temperature wasn't to my liking. It's like they left it out to cool before serving. Portion size was typical Filipino size, and the quality and quantity was so so. Nothing to write home about

main: Tony G’s Foodcourt by Ned Nanay’s Grill
title: Tony G's Foodcourt by Ned Nanay's Grill
Tgif
reviewr_text:
To day, January 7th 2019 my wife and I had lunch together in Cebu C Philippines 

I ordered the chicken burger and she a steak.  Service was average however, her meal was served with in a reasonable time and she was going to wait until my food arrived, but I told her to eat and she finished the meal and an additional 15 minutes went past waiting for my chicken burger.

So I sat and watched her eat and sometime later she sat and watched me eat. UNACCEPTABLE!

No one said anything about the huge amount of time difference between the meals. No explanation no aknowledgement that anything was wrong, REALLY? 
Even McDonald's does better than that. 

I asked to speak with the manager but my wife was tired of waiting and we left.  If I choose not to return you should know why.
Should I return,

FROM NOW ON I WILL NOTIFY THE SERVER, 
"I WILL REFUSE THE ORDER IF THEY ARE NOT DELIVERED WITHIN 2 MINUTES OF EACH OTHER"...

I don't want anything from TGIF, things happen, but not twice...

title: House of Lechon
reviewer_name: [{"reviewer_name":"Diego R."},{"reviewer_name":"Winlee W."},{"reviewer_name":"Carissa C."},{"reviewer_name":"Katrina C."},{"reviewer_name":"Edwin R."},{"reviewer_name":"Keith A."},{"reviewer_name":"Jerry H."},{"reviewer_name":"Val Y."},{"reviewer_name":"Evee N."},{"reviewer_name":"Joan N."},{"reviewer_name":"Gloria C."},{"reviewer_name":"Christy S."},{"reviewer_name":"Lina C."},{"reviewer_name":"Mark H."},{"reviewer_name":"Jonnah M."},{"reviewer_name":"Derek W."},{"reviewer_name":"Phil S."},{"reviewer_name":"Paulamertha A."},{"reviewer_name":"Benedict A."},{"reviewer_name":"Lynne C."}]
reviewr_text:
I heard about legends being famous in Cebu. I couldn't wait to try it. Well I'm in LA I found some Lechon being grilled over live coals at a street vending location. I tried it and it was excellent. I couldn't wait to get a chance to try it in Cebu. The first place I tried it was in the mall near where I was staying and it was decent but not as good as the in Manila. I decided to try House Of Lechon because of the reviews and because it was within walking distance to where I was staying. I was expecting it to be at least as good as what I had in Manila. I was a little bit disappointed however.  The Lechon was served cold but still not bad, not great but not bad.  A young lady soon came over and asked me w it was and I told her it was cold.  She took the plate and had it heated up, I assume in the microwave.  Parts were a little chewy likely due to the microwave.  Other pieces were very tender.  I am a fan of the skin but that was not very crisp so couldn't eat much of that.  Also probably due to the microwave. 

Overall I was a bit disappointed.  I don't think it was cooked over coals either.  The vegetable dish I ordered was very good. It reminded me of spinach.  I did have to find an employee to take my order but that is not unusual.  When I was ready to pay I just went to the cashier.  The place was very clean even the bathrooms.  They have a lot of seating indoors and out.  By the way the menu has much more than just Lechon or pork for that matter.

title: Ulli's
reviewer_name: [{"reviewer_name":"Sheena Y."},{"reviewer_name":"Brian J."},{"reviewer_name":"Jini O."},{"reviewer_name":"Jo Anne G."},{"reviewer_name":"Katrina E."},{"reviewer_name":"Lisa K."}]

title: Conching's Native Chicken
reviewr_text: Visiting Cebu City - my girlfriend raved about the Native Chicken and that we had to try it - so upon arriving in Cebu City my gf's cousin took us here... Not sure what authentic should feel like but this restaurant felt authentic considering I was the only foreigner there... One of the waiters is an interesting one - done up in a lot of make up and apparently very flirtatious and seems like he's a staple of the restaurant per their Facebook page... Anyway the native chicken cooked on these little grills but the chicken themselves are tiny - you probably need about one chicken a person. They have a lot of other grilled and friend foods including various fish - milkfish was the only one I recognized. We also tried the ceviche (local name I don't remember) but extremely good!! You should also try the puso which are the individually packaged rice which are local to cebu.... Very cool place and recommended if visiting,

title: Larsian BBQ
reviewer_name: [{"reviewer_name":"Julia C."},{"reviewer_name":"Christopher C."},{"reviewer_name":"M A G."},{"reviewer_name":"Edwin R."},{"reviewer_name":"Matthew S."},{"reviewer_name":"Sheena Y."},{"reviewer_name":"JessicaAllyn C."},{"reviewer_name":"Kent H."},{"reviewer_name":"Joey R."},{"reviewer_name":"Carlo L."},{"reviewer_name":"Fedd F."},{"reviewer_name":"Jeelyn D."},{"reviewer_name":"Janine D."},{"reviewer_name":"Michael C."},{"reviewer_name":"Emma D."}]
reviewr_text: A must eat for anyone traveling to the Cebu City area! Super affordable food for anyone on a budget but it's also one of the best bbq spots I've been to. There are many vendors to choose from! I've been told the taste is similar between all the vendors, so pick whichever spread appeals to you the most or whomever advertise their stand the best. They all have pork and chicken bbq, liempo, filipino chorizo, and all types of seafood! Rice is automatically placed on your table and you pay per puso rice. Honestly, it was also the most affordable bbq place we've been to.

title: 88 Degrees Cafe
reviewr_text: Cute coffee shop in Cebu where you can get yummy treats and of course coffee.  You can also get work done here and I think it's cute how they serve their coffee.  Great place to chill and chat with friends or get some studying done!

title: La Buona Italian Restaurant
reviewr_text: Saw this as one of the top Italian restaurants in Cebu on Travel Advisor. I finally saw a sign for it while driving down the back roads off Moldave toward Gorordo.  The pasta dishes are authentic and the pasta is cooked al dente. It was perfect. They also served a tastiest thin flour crisps. We had the Italian sausage pasta which was really good. The sauce was a bit creamy, perfect blend of spices and not too tangy.  The Asparagus creme soup was also very good. I just wish they had more bits of asparagus, because it could have also passed for a mushroom creme soup.  We were a bit surprised at the cost of the dish. It was about P500 a plate. We ended up sharing, but I kind of wish I had my own dish. I liked the food, but not sure if I'd go back because it was more then what I'd like to spend for Italian food. Very authentic though!

reviewr_text:

The downer is that wifi is limited to 2hours after a 100 peso purchase.
Whovever put the mall together was clever since there is a condo building closeby. Coffee is not bad, went with Americano coffee to hit the 100 mark

title: House of Lechon
reviewer_name: [{"reviewer_name":"Diego R."},{"reviewer_name":"Winlee W."},{"reviewer_name":"Carissa C."},{"reviewer_name":"Katrina C."},{"reviewer_name":"Edwin R."},{"reviewer_name":"Keith A."},{"reviewer_name":"Jerry H."},{"reviewer_name":"Val Y."},{"reviewer_name":"Evee N."},{"reviewer_name":"Joan N."},{"reviewer_name":"Gloria C."},{"reviewer_name":"Christy S."},{"reviewer_name":"Lina C."},{"reviewer_name":"Mark H."},{"reviewer_name":"Jonnah M."},{"reviewer_name":"Derek W."},{"reviewer_name":"Phil S."},{"reviewer_name":"Paulamertha A."},{"reviewer_name":"Benedict A."},{"reviewer_name":"Lynne C."}]
reviewr_text:
My mom and I went to the House of Lechon, which was part of our tour of Cebu. When we arrived around noon, the inside of the restaurant was packed. Luckily the restaurant was really big, and there was plenty of outdoor seating. Despite it being really hot and humid, the outdoor fans did a good job of making the temperature tolerable. I had an overall positive experience of the place. Customer service was good, and the food came out 15 min after we ordered. We ordered 1/4kg of spicy lechon, crispy chicken skin, mixed vegetables, and bam-I bisayas. 

I would definitely go as far saying that the House of Lechon's lechon was the best I've had... even better than lechon back at home in the US. The spicy lechon had such amazing flavor from all its seasonings. The skin was crispy, and the meat was very tender. 

Chicken skin is the best part of fried chicken, am I right?! Had to get it as the appetizer. It was exactly as advertised, and I was good with that.

The mixed vegetables dish was totally fine. I got it since I needed some vegetables in my life, so it was a plus that it more than exceeded my expectations. The vegetables included cabbage, broccoli, cauliflower, carrots, and bell peppers. They were all stir fried in oyster sauce. 

Lastly, the bam-I bisayas was delicious. It had a mix of bihon (skinny rice) noodles and Canton (thick egg) noodles. I'm used to pancit being dry, so I liked how this version of pancit was kind of soupy.

reviewr_text:
Review #041 - 2019

After checking in to our room and getting partly settled in, we decided to grab dinner before the restaurant closed for the night.

We showed up around 9 PM & were nicely greeted by the hostess out front.

Our server was also very friendly and accommodating.

I ordered the pepperoni pizza for my daughter, which she ate just the pepperoni.  The pizza is actually a little on the sweet side, which isn't my style.

I got the grilled salmon, which was actually very good.  It came with a side of ratatouille and puréed pumpkin, which was also very good.

This place offers both buffet style and a la carte so you can choose which fits your appetite.

Pretty good food and conveniently located inside our hotel!

title: Zark's Burgers
reviewr_text: The lettuce on the burger was rotten. I mean it not just welted but soggy rotten! It was ordered from the IT Park area. Clearly, they do not care about their customers. I would not take a second chance on this place again.

title: Hai Shin Lou
reviewr_text:

Service and ambiance good, dim sum not bad better than the fast food kiond of course but no stand out dishes, Fried taro dumpling not bad.

title: Zark's Burgers
reviewr_text: Not quite good as a high end burger place in the US, but they are headed in the right direction. Best burger in Cebu. Interesting combinations. Cayenne Burger from Hell. Bacon wrapped bun the on another.

title: Birdseed
reviewer_name: [{"reviewer_name":"John L."},{"reviewer_name":"Kent H."},{"reviewer_name":"Maya S."},{"reviewer_name":"Toyo M."},{"reviewer_name":"Alan S."},{"reviewer_name":"Carl V."},{"reviewer_name":"Sheena Y."},{"reviewer_name":"Rustum N."},{"reviewer_name":"Cha S."},{"reviewer_name":"ravi b."},{"reviewer_name":"Paula T."},{"reviewer_name":"Chris M."},{"reviewer_name":"Pablo G."}]
reviewr_text: My first meal was the "big breakfast" and instantly i fell in love with Birdseed.  I'm kinda fond of their brown rice which they cook just the way i like it. Not too soft/soggy nor too tough, just perfect.  Other must-tries: Salmon Silog and Chicken Pomodoro.  I'll definitely be back for more good eats.

title: Lighthouse Restaurant
reviewr_text:
We probably would've never eaten here if we were on our own.  Why?  Because it's on the second floor of a mall & never would have seen it.  But our tour guide brought us there as part of our package.  It nice & clean - - they even had a 2 piece band playing music during lunch!!!

The food was basically ordered for us before we got there.  Soup with clams in their shells & veggies.  Cubed pork, kang-kong, shrimp, & stuffed crabs were all tasty.  My wife enjoyed the roasted chicken in pandan leaves the best.  My choice was baked tahong (mussels) with cheese & garlic - - a little bit too cheesy for me, but still tasty.

Fresh mango shakes hit the spot on a hot day!!!

Enjoy.

title: La Cantina
reviewr_text:
La Cantina is the Best lunch restaurant in the area! It's located right behind The Rose Pharmacy in Arcada 5 office complex on Tipolo Highway. 

Sam and Hedi run the show here and are absolutely amazing! They always provide several healthy options, and several comfort options. They rotate dishes daily, providing vegetarian, meat and fish foods to choose from. 

La Cantina opens early and offers breakfast, too, but we're most often here for lunch (when I'm working in Cebu). 

See ya there!

reviewer_name: [{"reviewer_name":"Cha S."},{"reviewer_name":"Alvin K."},{"reviewer_name":"Wok Star X."},{"reviewer_name":"Rhoel P."},{"reviewer_name":"Toyo M."}]

title: Azul
reviewr_text:
This place is a cooking and learning experience and another locals favorite.  It's less than a mile from Marco Polo Plaza Hotel. 

You order at the counter,  and they provide the ingredients sauce for you to cook in the wok. Azul also provides a one burner, portable stove. Once cooked, you then dip then sauce with "Puso" - a rice, covered and braided with bamboo leaves,  cooked slowly in coconut water.  This rice dish is only found in Cebu, and it's what the locals eat daily as their rice staple. Best to also eat with your hands.  It's how the locals eat it.

There are instructions how to cook the sauce at the wall. Azul also has inihaw (grilled in charcoal), cooked squid, seafood, and the famous Filipino Sisig dish,  made from parts of chicken and pig. I was surprised they also provide dim sum and they cook this for you.  Actually,  it was delicious. There are indoor and outdoor dining area, but it's best to eat outside as it can get warm indoors. 

If you are in the area, this place should not be missed and should be in your local foodie itinerary. 

Cheers!

title: La Nostra Pizzeria Napoletana
reviewr_text:
Very good pizza in a nice upscale restaurant. It is expensive my Filipino standard, ranging 500-700 php per pizza, but you can tell the ingredients are top notch. The pizza oven is really cool, too.
My only minor complaint is that the pizza was a bit sparse on toppings. For example, only two basil leaves that were left whole and not spread around to all the pieces. The flavor of the crust and sauce more than made up for it, tho. 
I'd come back whenever I'm in the mood for high quality fire burned pizza. 
Might see ya there!

reviewr_text: We ordered the Shoyu and the Tonkatsu ramen as well as a side ordering edamame and takoyaki. Everything was above average, although with such great options for ramen nowadays, I'm almost always expecting amazing. I know, it's not fair which is why I changed my three stars to a four stars and back to a three. In a vacuum, this place is rated much higher than I rated.

title: Handuraw
reviewr_text:
Handuraw is one of the best hangout spots in Cebu. The staff is the best and always makes us feel so cared about. There is regularly live music in the later evening, but if it's not your jam, just sit outside and it's quieter. Really supportive of the community, local artists, the environment, and Cebu.
The thin crust pizza is delicious. It's very unique, so don't expect classic Italian thin crust or you'll be disappointed. But to me, this is Cebu's pizza. I'm vegetarian so I usually get cheesy cheese with added pineapple. But the Handuraw special is the must-try classic. Besides pizza, there's a menu of other local favorites.
Have a beer, a pizza, and enjoy good company and the best vibes!!

title: Cafe Chips
reviewr_text: Decent cafe upstairs on the 7th floor of the Copenhagen residences. The staff are very friendly and the food is good. We went and had breakfast for dinner, because when are eggs and tocino not good?!

reviewer_name: [{"reviewer_name":"Colby W."},{"reviewer_name":"Sheena Y."},{"reviewer_name":"Brian J."},{"reviewer_name":"Thomas K."},{"reviewer_name":"Angela L."},{"reviewer_name":"Monz S."}]
reviewr_text:
My family has the habit if calling in for reservations. On Saturday nights, we usually call ahead and reserve for a big group of at least 13 people. There was a mix-up when we arrived, apparently our reservation table had been given away. We were late for about 15 minutes. The waiter claimed that since we were late, they had to give the table away. My cousin argued that it should have been proper for the restaurant to call us before giving our table away.

Luckily, we didn't wait long (about 15 mins) until two tables opened up to accommodate us. Other than that little mix-up, this is one of the better Shabu Shabu houses in Cebu. Their cuttlefish ball, squid ball, beef with mushroom ball, and several cuts of beef and pork are some of the better quality. Making your own sauce is always one of the highlights for everyone before the meal is served. The kids enjoy it, and even the older adults. The service is pretty fast, and time is just taken up by cooking your own meats and vegetables. It's not just fun, but it's also a healthy choice.

Tip: Sweet Little Things next door is great for your sweet tooth fix after the meal.

title: Puso Bistro and Bar
reviewer_name: [{"reviewer_name":"Jessica S."},{"reviewer_name":"Sivilay T."},{"reviewer_name":"Cha S."},{"reviewer_name":"Ian Jude F."},{"reviewer_name":"Toyo M."}]
reviewr_text:
Puso is the restaurant located inside Quest Hotel and Conference Center. They function primarily in a buffet format, but you do have the option of ordering a la carte. Obviously, if you order room service, as I did on one particular night, you order a la carte. For room service, I had the Grouper/ Lapu Lapu in Banana Leaf (PHP 528) smothered in coconut cream. The "cream" certainly was on the thinner side and somewhat bland, but it provided a much lighter meal than anticipated for a late-night which was welcomed. Jasmine rice on the side was added on as extra. 

We went down on another occasion for breakfast as it was still the more convenient option considering that in order to get to Ayala mall, one must cross a very busy street with a high potential for death. Their *Tapsilog* was grilled perfectly with the inclusion and added flavoring of sauteed veggies. With the usual garlic rice and two eggs, they served a pickled atchara on the side. Dishes are a little pricier here, but you suck it up since it's the most accessible option. The atmosphere seems more high-end, but one is still able to walk-in casually and still receive utmost customer service. Plenty of tourists here as it is in a 3-star hotel.

title: Kimstaurant
reviewr_text: Finally! I got to try this place. It just opened recently around July of this year but I never had the chance to try it out; and now that I finally had the chance...it didn't disappoint! The place and ambience was modern and blended in with the other restaurants in the area. There weren't too many banchan offerings though but that wasn't a problem. The important thing is that as long as they have good kimchi, I'm good with that. The food was astounding! They're as authentic as you can get. One notable dish was their Beef Galbi Jjim. Out of all the Korean restaurants I've been to here in Cebu, this is the only one that has legit Beef Galbi Jjim. The other dishes I tried are worth mentioning as well; the pork from the Osam Bulgogi and Jeauk Bokkem was tasty, tender, and of good quality while the Duenjang Jjigae (soup) was flavorful and boiling hot (just what I like and what it should be). The Mandu (dumplings) was juicy and the ratio of meat was balanced well with the wrapper. The Jajangmyun was as expected. It wasn't the best I had but still satisfactory. To finish it all off, they gladly offered a complimentary Korean fish shaped ice cream sandwich called Samanco. Overall, I'd definitely come back again and also try their other dishes.

reviewr_text: This place was very disappointing.  Lechon was very cold. All the food were very salty, my tongue was numb after I ate, Didn't realize the saltiness because I was hungry.  Service was ok. I will never recommend this place if you're watching your salt intake. The food was below average from all the places I've been.  Have to look for another lechon place tomorrow. Lol!

title: Yakimix
reviewr_text:
This place used be a little better. The food is okay but plentiful and probably worth the reasonable prices. Cooking your own food is neat. 
The service however, is not great. They say they are open until 11pm but around 9:00ish they stopped replacing any of the food trays. Some waiter turned off our grill even though we were still getting food and did not even bother to bus our dishes. And to top it off they turned off the 2 ACs near us. We had to ask them to turn everything back on. I guess they REALLY want you out the door asap. We were not able to talk to a manager or supervisor because they were at a different site that day, which begs the question why not have a manager PER restaurant. but whatever.
Well, job done, I'm never coming back here and recommending all my friends to avoid this buffet.

title: Top of Cebu
reviewer_name: [{"reviewer_name":"Keith A."},{"reviewer_name":"Marco R."},{"reviewer_name":"Caitlin M."},{"reviewer_name":"Sivilay T."},{"reviewer_name":"Tawny T."},{"reviewer_name":"Kartik K."}]
reviewr_text: We hired a taxi driver for the day to bang out all the tourist sites and ended our long touristy day with a delicious meal here. Menu is expansive, food is good and the views might be the best of Cebu. The restaurant itself is huge and would be great for a large party. We ordered the truffled mushroom seasonal pasta, seafood fondue, spring rolls, steak and garlic butter sauteed clams. We definitely walked out satisfied.

title: Sunburst Fried Chicken
reviewr_text: Good old classic favorites. Sunburst has been around for so many years now and up to now it's been a household favorite. Their fried chicken is absolutely one of the best (in my opinion) in the city..or better yet..in the country. My family has been a repeat customer ever since. We usually eat here on Sundays together. We usually order the chicken crackers(crispy chicken skin), fried liver and gizzard, sotanghon guisado(vermicelli noodles), calamares (squid rings deep fried in batter), and we each order a chicken meal for ourselves. So far this has been one of the best "american style" fried chicken in the country and I know many agree as well.

title: Shawarma
reviewr_text:
When visiting the Philippines, one of things on my to eat list is a Shawarma.  What is a shawarma?  It is a Middle Eastern dish consisting of meat cut into thin slices, and it is roasted on a slow turning vertical rotisserie or spit.  For some reason I always crave Shawarmas when we go to Cebu even though it is not a Native dish.

When I saw the Shawarma place at SM City Cebu mall, I just had to check it out.  They have a very limited menu.  All they sell are two Shawarma Wraps.  Either Original or Bbq flavors, and you can add cheese for a few more pesos.  I was hoping they would have lamb as one of their choices, but all they had was beef.  So I ordered their Original Beef Shawarma Wrap with all the toppings/fillings and spicy sauce.  Sat down at their one table, and ate my Wrap.  It was yummy!  I liked it so much that I ordered two more wraps to go.  Tasted even better the next day!!    

If you have not tried Shawarma, you need to cause you are missing out on some good food!!

reviewr_text: A must stop place when in cebu! local, good food,  and affordable! you have a lot of options here. there's so many food stalls to choose from and you can pick almost anything (meat and seafood) to be barbecued! the location itself is centralized. it's by the fuente osmena circle. if you are new in cebu, you can pretty much ask anyone and they will lead you there. definitely a place to check out!

title: Tim Ho Wan
reviewer_name: [{"reviewer_name":"Phil S."},{"reviewer_name":"Marissa S."},{"reviewer_name":"Toyo M."},{"reviewer_name":"Cynthia Q."},{"reviewer_name":"Tracy N."},{"reviewer_name":"Ray J."}]
reviewr_text:
I was really sour about The Halal Guys opening first in the Philippines before LA so when I heard the same story with Tim Ho Wan, it came as no surprise to me anymore. In a way I lucked out as I was able to finally try the famed BAKED BBQ PORK BUNS on my last trip to Cebu without having to wait in agony for their doors to open at Diamond Jamboree Plaza, Irvine. Served hot and fresh, a tip is to break it apart first to let the steam come out and cool down a bit before touching your lips. The bread itself is glorious with high marks on texture and taste while the bbq pork was sweet, savory, and just delicious. For this alone, now I understand why the Hong Kong location has been awarded a Michelin star; the cheapest restaurant yet.

Featuring mainly dim sum dishes, I pleasantly devoured their siumai, vermicelli roll with shrimp, pan fried radish cake, spare ribs rice, wasabi prawn dumpling, and dumpling in spicy sauce. I wouldn't say they're the best I've had as most are comparable to what I can get from Chinese restaurants here, some even better. 

So long as you're here for those buns, you won't be disappointed. True story.

reviewr_text:
This restaurant is a famous house of lechon in town. Referring to a suckling pig that is roasted. The pig is cooked by skewering the entire animal, entrails removed, on a large stick and cooking it in a pit filled with charcoal. The pig is placed over the charcoal, and the stick or rod it is attached to is turned in a rotisserie action. The pig is roasted on all sides for several hours until done. The process of cooking and basting usually results in making the pork skin crisp and is a distinctive feature of the dish.

Prior to arrival, I heard nothing but goodness about this place. I've lived in this area quite long time ago but never tried the lechon probably I wasn't adventurous enough as I am today. I was excited to be back in town along with my brother and sisters. We've been out early doing a usual tourist stuff and it was lunch time when we decided to visit the place.

 Upon entering we're greeted with one of the staff. It was a little busy, luckily there was one table waiting for us. We were directly seated and order.  As for visit , we order the famous lechon, pinakbet ( made from mixed vegetables in steamed fish or shrimp paste ), and diniguan  ( pork blood stew ). I thought the entire dish was delicious. The lechon itself was extremely well seasoned. The meat was tender and the skin was crispy. I love every bite of it. As for dessert, we ordered the ube cheesecake and special halo-halo. It was creamy and tastel absolutely divine.

What a great visit. I also have to commend the fantastic customer service. The staff was knowledgeable about the menu. Very friendly and polite. I will definitely come back

title: Yakski
reviewr_text: This is a homegrown favorite as far as i know. The original location is in the Capitol area, but I've heard about this place for about the last two years and now they were clever enough to open a location in it park. The setup seems simple, big open space and barbecue area on corner. They were also clever to isolate the barbecue area like a smoking room so you don't smell like barbecue after a meal.  It has to be in the sauce or choice of meat since it visually looks the same except for the saice they use which is dark black ad opposed to the typical bright red. But despite the plenty of barbecue places om cebu this place seems to be popular and becoming a neighborhood favorite.

title: CnT Lechon
reviewr_text:
Reading other Yelp reviews *ahem Joey R* I learned this was Cebu's most popular chain for lechon (roast pig for the non-Tagalog speaking folks.) 

Our local driver took us to this branch across from SM Cebu City. It's a bit unassuming as it's in a yellow building on top of a parking garage!

A decent amount of locals came in for a weekday lunch. I wasn't in charge of the ordering but we just tried their lechon and nothing else.

I was a bit disappointed with the skin, as I was hoping it'd be crispy and fatty juicy. Instead it was a bit tough and hard to chew. But the actual meat itself was delicious. Mix it with patis or suka and you're good to go.

If you're ever in Cebu, CnT is a good starter for a taste of Cebu's specialty lechon!

title: KPub BBQ
reviewr_text:
Nice and new, but just average. Food is "Asian" but nothing really stands out. At the table was tong samgyeopsal, whole pork belly, deeper samgyeopsal, Korean style bacon, and deaehi bulgogi, marinated pork slice in sweet soy sauce. To be honest, there were no standouts, but luckily nothing was horrible. I took a pic of the "pick your meat". Any one of those picks were P150 plus more.  The wait staff were confused and when I asked for a refill of the kimchi, it never returned. 
So in summary, food 3/5, service 1/5, ambiance/ decor 4/5. 
Not trying to be authentic. Less than average.

reviewr_text:
I've been to Hawaii and I'm obsessed with the food. So when I found out there's a Hawaiian restaurant in the Philippines, I got super excited. 

The food is good, it's Hawaii good, but definitely good enough. 

I was more excited with the fact this restaurant has in upstairs area. It's basically a tree house style. The ambiance is amazing. 

Definitely get the loco moco and the short ribs! And bring some friends and have some drinks. Great place to hang out at night!

title: UCC Cafe Terrace
reviewr_text:
I looked forward to this place FOREVER because I loved the canned UCC coffee available in the states.

I tried the iced coffee blend with warm milk. Personally, I didn't care for it. I guess because the coffee doesn't melt fast enough and the coffee:milk ratio was off, it was largely a glass of milk.

Get their brewed coffee. Some of the best coffee I had in my life! Food wasn't bad, but they were completely out of the first three things I tried to order. I liked their combination of French and Japanese fare. Service was great too, and you can summon them from a button if you're upstairs.

title: Mooon Cafe
reviewr_text:
This restaurant is one of my favorite mexican restaurant.
I took so many dishes here and the best one is Breaded fish fillet. Deep fried fish fillet is sooooo tender and juicy, seasoning is also perfect.
If you are planning to visit here, I definitely recommend this dish.
I just wrote about the fish, the other dishes are also very good though.
